  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SHO Nile Hope Nyirol - FSL and WASH</narrative>
  </title>
  <description akvo:type="4" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Famine and livelihood response Nyirol</narrative>
  </description>
  <description akvo:type="6" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The food security situation in South Sudan continues to deteriorate with an estimated 5.5 million people projected to be severely food insecure by July 2017.  Nyirol County is also among the 14 counties with Global Acute Malnutrition (GAM) at or above 15%.  Together, these facts present a worsening food security and nutrition situation. There is therefore an urgent need to scale up interventions in Food Security and WASH sectors to address the immediate needs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description akvo:type="5" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This action is intended to target 1500 households of the affected IDPs and host communities. Limited WASH services and increased vulnerability of displaced populations will increase the potential for disease outbreak. The nutritional status is severely impacted by diarrhoea and other water related diseases. lack of improved sanitation and limited knowledge of hygiene practices increase their vulnerability, especially for children under 2.</narrative>
  </description>
